name: F. G. Book et al. v. M. J. Day & Robert C. Sharpe. Appeal of Whitney, Wabel & Co.

judges: Before Green, Williams, McCollum, Mitchell, Dean and Fell, JJ.
parties: F. G. Book et al. v. M. J. Day & Robert C. Sharpe. Appeal of Whitney, Wabel & Co.

opinions.text:
Opinion by
Mr. Justice Mitchell,
This case was argued -with Claflin’s Appeal, opinion filed herewith, ante, p. 44, and for the reasons there given the order of the court below is reversed, and the rule for an issue reinstated and made absolute, costs to abide the final judgment.
opinions.author: Mr. Justice Mitchell,

casebody.head_matter:
F. G. Book et al. v. M. J. Day & Robert C. Sharpe. Appeal of Whitney, Wabel & Co.
Argued Oct. 17, 1898.
Appeal, No. 45, Oct. T., 1898, by-Whitney, Wabel & Co., from order of C. P. Lawrence Co., March T., 1898, No. 1, discharging rule for interpleader.
Before Green, Williams, McCollum, Mitchell, Dean and Fell, JJ.
Reversed.
January 2, 1899:
